<h2 class="section-heading">Why Clubs Matter</h2>
<p>The main aims of clubs and societies at MHSK include educating, stimulating thinking, doing research, entertaining, developing creativity, rendering services to oneself and society, providing avenues for socialization, helping students grow spiritually and morally, and helping them develop and exploit their gifts and talents.</p>

<p>All students are encouraged to join at least <strong>two clubs</strong>: one academic and one non-academic. Our school has continuously excelled in club-related activities and competitions both nationally and internationally participating in Wildlife, President's Award Scheme, Mathematics, World Scholars, Chess, Red Cross, St. John Ambulance, and Science clubs among many others.</p>

